<h2>The weather in February 2021</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
In February 2021 the temperature in southern Europe was (exceptionally) much above average, whereas the the temperature in northern Europe was much below average (figure 5). As the average temperature in southern Europa is higher than the average temperature in northern Europe, the south-to-north temperature gradient in February was much higher than average. The temperatures of the warmest day were (exceptionally) above average almost everywhere in Europe (figure 7, right panel), even in northern Europe where the average temperatures were below average.
