<h3>Precipitation</h3>
<br><br>
Precipitation in February 2021 was (exceptionally) above average in parts of eastern and northern Europe, particularly in Ukraine, and in Portugal (figure 10). In the Baltic states and southern Sweden precipitation was (exceptionally) below normal. The pattern of the monthly precipitation is quite similar to the pattern of the highest 5-day sum, indicating that most of the monthly precipitation fell in those 5 days (figure 11). In Portugal a large part of the monthly precipitation fell on the day with the highest 1-day sum.
