<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
<br><br>
Global radiation in February 2021 was above average in most of Europe, particularly in France (figure 12, right panel). Cloud cover was below normal in most of Europe (figure 14, right panel). The cloud cover pattern is generally in line with the global radiation pattern, although the cloud cover anomaly over France is not as low as would be expected from the positive radiation anomaly.
